CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 28, 1970, pg. 11 reads: "Set For Show Down - Friday is the big day for both the Fifth Avenue and Schenley High School basketball teams when they meet in a game that may eventually decide the City League Champions for 1970. Fifth is unbeaten in city league pay and Schenley has lost only once and that to Fifth...  The Schenley starting five is composed of, from left, Anthony Coleman ,Carmel Stewart, Clarence Hopson and Maurice Lucas.  Sitting with the ball is Jeffrey Matthews.  Harris Photos"
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of five Schenley High School basketball players, standing, left to right: Anthony Coleman, Carmel Stewart, Clarence Hopson and Maurice Lucas; seated holding basketball ball: Jeffrey Matthews
